QUESTION:
SOLUTION:
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
TIME  COMPLEXITY:O(n)
SPACE COMPLEXITY:O(n)
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Step 1: First identify that it is a stack problem
Step 2: Loop through the values and push any value that is >0
Step 3: If not then there are three conditions you should look into.
          -> If the stack is not empty and the top element in the stack is > 0 and the top element is < the -(-ve element) 5< -(-6)
          -> Loop through until you keep finding a positive value that is lesser than the current negative value.
          -> Once the while loop is done, check if the stack is empty or the top element is <0 push the current element
          ->if the peek element is == the number then pop 
Step 4: Loop through and create the array.
          
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
CODE:
class Solution {
    public int[] asteroidCollision(int[] asteroids) {
        Stack<Integer>st=new Stack<>();
        for(int num:asteroids){
            if(num>0)st.push(num);
            else {
                while(!st.isEmpty() && st.peek()>0 && st.peek()<-num)st.pop();
                if(st.isEmpty() || st.peek()<0)st.push(num);
                if(st.peek()==-num)st.pop();
            }
        }
        int res[]=new int[st.size()];
        int size=st.size()-1;
        while(!st.isEmpty()){
            res[size--]=st.pop();
        }
        return res;
    }
}
